        "setup": "Create or open an app in [Your Apps](https://api.slack.com/apps), enable **Socket Mode**, then under **Basic Information** generate an app-level token. Slack's Socket Mode guide says this token is used with `apps.connections.open` to obtain a temporary WebSocket URL.",
        "acquisition": "manual"
      },
      "slack_cli_login": {
        "type": "compound",
        "label": "Slack CLI workspace login",
        "generateUrl": "https://docs.slack.dev/tools/slack-cli/guides/authorizing-the-slack-cli",
        "setup": "Install the Slack CLI, then run `slack login`. The CLI shows a `/slackauthticket ...` slash command to paste into a Slack conversation, after which you confirm permissions in Slack and paste the returned challenge code back into the terminal. The CLI stores credentials in `~/.slack/credentials.json`.",
        "acquisition": "manual"
      },
      "slack_service_token": {
        "type": "bearer",
        "label": "Slack CLI service token",
        "generateUrl": "https://docs.slack.dev/tools/slack-cli/guides/authorizing-the-slack-cli",
        "setup": "Use the Slack CLI authorization flow in [Authorizing the Slack CLI](https://docs.slack.dev/tools/slack-cli/guides/authorizing-the-slack-cli) to mint a long-lived service token for CI/CD: run `slack auth token`, complete the `slackauthticket` exchange in Slack, copy the token shown in the terminal, then authorize the CLI with `slack login --auth <your-service-token>`.",
        "acquisition": "manual"
